Here's a `ProductDetailViewModel` using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm (recommended approach):

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Simulate async data fetch
        await Task.Delay(500);
        Name = "Widget Pro";
        Price = 29.99m;
        IsAvailable = true;
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public `Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable` properties (with `PropertyChanged` notification) and a `LoadCommand` (`IAsyncRelayCommand`).

**XAML usage with compiled bindings:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel">
    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='In Stock: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding LoadCommand.IsRunning}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**
- `x:DataType` at page root enables compiled bindings (8–20× faster, AOT-safe)
- `[ObservableProperty]` auto-generates `INotifyPropertyChanged` plumbing
- `[RelayCommand]` on an `async Task` method generates `LoadCommand` with built-in `IsRunning` for busy indicators
- Setting properties from `LoadAsync` is safe — MAUI marshals `PropertyChanged` to the UI thread automatically

**NuGet:** `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (>= 8.2)
